OL,3,CSewage burst prompts no swim warning
OL,4,Cas temperatures soar
OL,6,FAn Environment Agency Spokesperson
OL,7,Fsaid: "Our officers have been
OL,8,Fmonitoring Southern Water's repair to
OL,9,Fa sewage line which burst last night.
OL,11,F"As a precaution, we issued guidance
OL,12,Fagainst bathing at Lee on Solent. The
OL,13,Fpollution was stopped in the early
OL,14,Fhours of the morning.
OL,16,F"Today we were on site to monitor
OL,17,FSouthern Water's progress with
OL,18,Frepairs. We will update Swimfo when
OL,19,Fbathing advice is lifted."
